The paper deals with the problem of load balancing in distributed spatial streaming systems, which involves processing massive amounts of spatial data in real-time. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), networked information systems (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given that the paper proposes a protocol for load balancing in distributed systems, cs.DC and cs.SY are less likely, while cs.DB, cs.DS, and cs.NI are more likely.
